LABEL: HLA-E wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-E wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p22.1. This allele encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, alpha chain E protein.

LABEL: MHC Class II Gene
SYNONYMS: Class II MHC|MHC Class II|MHC Class II Gene
definition: A family of genes expressed mainly by antigen presenting cells that encode major histocompatibility complex proteins and are involved in the presentation of fragments from phagocytized extracellular proteins to cytotoxic lymphocytes.

LABEL: MHC Class I Gene
SYNONYMS: Class I MHC|MHC Class I|MHC Class I Gene
definition: A family of genes that encode major histocompatibility complex proteins and are involved in the presentation of cytoplasmic protein fragments to cytotoxic lymphocytes.

LABEL: Major Histocompatibility Complex Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA Complex Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex Gene
definition: A group of linked loci, collectively termed H-2 complex in the mouse and HLA complex in humans, that codes for cell-surface histocompatibility antigens and is the principal determinant of tissue type and transplant compatibility.

LABEL: HLA-DRB1 Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-DRB1|HLA-DRB1|HLA-DRB1 Gene|HLA-DRB1 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DR Beta 1 Gene
definition: This gene is involved in immunoregulation and antigen presentation. The gene has several hundred alleles and polymorphism typing is routinely performed for bone marrow and kidney transplantation.

LABEL: HLA-A Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-A|HLA-A|HLA-A|HLA-A Gene|HLA-A Gene|HLA-A Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class I, A Gene
definition: This gene is involved in immune responses and histocompatibility processes.

LABEL: HLA-DPB1 Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-DPB1|HLA-DPB1|HLA-DPB1 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DP Beta 1 Gene
definition: This gene plays a critical regulatory role in antigen presentation and peptide binding specificity.

LABEL: HLA-A wt Allele
SYNONYMS: HLA-A wt Allele|HLA-A wt Allele|HLAA|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class I, A wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-A wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, A-1 alpha chain protein, is involved in immune system peptide presentation.

LABEL: HLA-DRB1 wt Allele
SYNONYMS: DRB Gene|HLA DRB1|HLA-DRB1 wt Allele|HLA-DRB1 wt Allele|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DR Beta 1 wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-DRB1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 11 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB1-4 beta chain protein, plays a role in the mediation of antigen presentation.

LABEL: HLA-DPB1 wt Allele
SYNONYMS: HLA-DP1B|HLA-DPB1 wt Allele|HLADPB1|MHC DPB1|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DP Beta 1 wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-DPB1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 24 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DP(W4) beta chain protein, is involved in the modulation of antigen presentation.

LABEL: HLA-C Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-C|HLA-C|HLA-C Gene|HLA-C Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class I, C Gene
definition: This gene plays a role in both immune responses and histocompatibility processes.

LABEL: HLA-C wt Allele
SYNONYMS: D6S204|HLA-C wt Allele|HLA-C wt Allele|HLA-JY3|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class I, C wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-C wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, Cw-1 alpha chain protein, plays a role in antigen presentation and the immune response.

LABEL: HLA-B Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-B|HLA-B|HLA-B Gene|HLA-B Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class I, B Gene
definition: This gene plays a role in both immune responses and histocompatibility processes.

LABEL: HLA-B wt Allele
SYNONYMS: HLA-B wt Allele|HLA-B wt Allele|HLAB|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class I, B wt Allele
definition: HLA-B wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, B-7 alpha chain protein, plays a role in peptide presentation by the immune system. Certain allelic variants of the HLA-B gene are associated with susceptibility to ankylosing spondylitis, carbamazepine-induced Stevens-Johnson syndrome and allopurinol-induced severe cutaneous adverse reaction.

LABEL: HLA-DQB1 Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-DQB1|HLA-DQB1|HLA-DQB1 Gene|HLA-DQB1 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DQ Beta 1 Gene
definition: This gene is involved in the mediation of antigen presentation.

definition: Human HLA-DQB1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DQ beta 1 chain protein, plays a role in the regulation of antigen presentation.

LABEL: HLA-DRB3 Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-DRB3|HLA-DRB3|HLA-DRB3 Gene|HLA-DRB3 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DR Beta 3 Gene
definition: This gene is involved in immunoregulation and antigen presentation.

LABEL: HLA-DRB3 wt Allele
SYNONYMS: HLA-DR3B|HLA-DRB3 wt Allele|HLA-DRB3 wt Allele|Human Leucocyte Antigen DRB3|Human Leukocyte Antigen DRB3|MGC117330|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DR Beta 3 wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-DRB3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 13 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB3 beta chain protein, is involved in the mediation of antigen presentation and stimulation of the immune response. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

LABEL: HLA-DRB4 Gene

definition: Human HLA-DRB4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 15 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB4 beta chain protein, plays a role in the regulation of antigen presentation. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

LABEL: HLA-DRB5 Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-DRB5|HLA-DRB5|HLA-DRB5 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DR Beta 5 Gene
definition: This gene is involved in the regulation of T-cell-mediated immunity and antigen presentation.

LABEL: HLA-DRB5 wt Allele
SYNONYMS: HLA-DRB5 wt Allele|Human Leucocyte Antigen DRB5|Human Leukocyte Antigen DRB5|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DR Beta 5 wt Allele
definition: Human HLA-DRB5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 13 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB5 beta chain protein, is involved in the modulation both of antigen presentation and the immune response. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

LABEL: HLA-DQA1 Gene
SYNONYMS: HLA-DQA1|HLA-DQA1|HLA-DQA1 Gene|HLA-DQA1 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DQ Alpha 1 Gene
definition: This gene plays a role in antigen presentation and immunoregulation.

LABEL: HLA-DQA1 wt Allele
SYNONYMS: CD|CELIAC1|DQ-A1|FLJ27088|FLJ27328|GSE|HLA DQA1|HLA-DQA|HLA-DQA1 wt Allele|HLA-DQA1 wt Allele|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DQ Alpha 1 wt Allele

SYNONYMS: HLA-DPA1|HLA-DPA1|HLA-DPA1 Gene|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DP Alpha 1 Gene

SYNONYMS: DASS-32K24.2|HLA DP1A|HLA-DPA1 wt Allele|HLADP|HLASB|Major Histocompatibility Complex, Class II, DP Alpha 1 wt Allele

LABEL: HLA-F Gene
